title: Grateful Dead Live at Kiel Auditorium on 1981-07-08
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step-> Feel Like A Stranger, Peggy-O-> Little Red Rooster, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Don't Ease Me In, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Franklin's Tower-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Finally We now have a top notch recording of this show,  only took 36 years to hear it Worth the wait though. Frank you did an outstanding job recording all the shows I have listened to as of late. I hope you post a better version of the 1st show on this tour from the Summit in Houston . From what I have heard over the years this recording is finally the kind that when popped in a tape recorder back in the day everyone would say WOW where is this from?  Just looking at the set list is enough to be envious but now we can all share the pleasure.
 Again thank you for your hard work recording these for our listening pleasure so many years later.  
 5 stars because it is very good sounding and because I hope 5 stars attracts others to listen.
Happy Thanksgiving all
